<subSubSection id="C3086577D563FFD4FEA5E05C5DC9FB13" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BAD36FCD563FFD4FEA5E05C5DC9FB13" blockId="7.[264,1325,918,1870]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<emphasis id="B966EAEED563FFD4FEA5E05C5F8AFB9A" bold="true" box="[312,432,1038,1064]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName id="4C124D7FD563FFD4FE22E05D5CBCFB9A" box="[447,646,1039,1064]" class="Insecta" family="Scatopsidae" genus="Anapausis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wirthi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B966EAEED563FFD4FE22E05D5CBCFB9A" box="[447,646,1039,1064]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Anapausis wirthi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B966EAEED563FFD4FD10E05C5CD1FB9A" bold="true" box="[653,747,1038,1064]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A2555795D563FFD4FD10E05C5CD1FB9A" box="[653,747,1038,1064]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
can be separated from other species of the genus by the shape of the gonostyle, especially its dorsal arm, by the bifid paramere, and by the shape of S 
<number id="3DDA24DBD563FFD4FE1CE00D5FA5FBCB" box="[385,415,1119,1145]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="10.0">10</number>
divided into a pair of independent sclerites, with a rounded tooth close to the apex. The vesica is largely developed. There are no meral setae.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3086577D563FFD9FEA5E0FC5C23FEEC" lastPageId="10" lastPageNumber="11" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BAD36FCD563FFD4FEA5E0FC5FF3FB7A" blockId="7.[264,1325,918,1870]" box="[312,457,1198,1224]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<emphasis id="B966EAEED563FFD4FEA5E0FC5FF3FB7A" bold="true" box="[312,457,1198,1224]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Description</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BAD36FCD563FFD4FEA5E0855B1EFB43" blockId="7.[264,1325,918,1870]" box="[312,1316,1239,1265]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<emphasis id="B966EAEED563FFD4FEA5E0855F46FB42" box="[312,380,1239,1264]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Male.</emphasis>
Measurements (in mm). Body length, 2.28; wing length, 1.46; wing width, 0.64.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BAD36FCD563FFDBFEA5E0AD5DE4FE34" blockId="7.[264,1325,918,1870]" lastBlockId="8.[264,1323,284,390]" lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="9" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
Color. Regularly dark brown, light brown transverse strip on all femora and tibiae. Head elliptical, macrotrichia reaching anterior ¼ of occiput, microtrichia present; eyebridge complete; flagellum with 
<number id="3DDA24DBD563FFD4FD13E11D5CA7FADB" box="[654,669,1359,1385]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="8.0">8</number>
articles, single regular whorl of setae per flagellomere except for distal one with 
<number id="3DDA24DBD563FFD4FDA7E1255C73FA23" box="[570,585,1399,1425]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="2.0">2</number>
whorls; mesal ocellus much smaller than lateral 
<number id="3DDA24DBD563FFD4FB15E1255AA3FA23" box="[1160,1177,1399,1425]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="2.0">2</number>
; no setae on front above antennae; labella small, maxillary palpus well developed, slender to apex, covered with setae and microtrichia, sensory pits and sensillae absent; cardo well developed. Thorax. Antepronotal setae, 
<number id="3DDA24DBD563FFD4FC94E1BD5D6CF9BB" box="[777,854,1519,1545]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="42.5" valueMax="47.0" valueMin="38.0">38–47</number>
; proepisternals, 
<number id="3DDA24DBD563FFD4FBB6E1BD5A71F9BB" box="[1067,1099,1519,1545]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="13.0">13</number>
; proepimerals, 
<number id="3DDA24DBD563FFD4FA8BE1BD5B1DF9BB" box="[1302,1319,1519,1545]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="9.0">9</number>
; spiracular sclerite setae, 
<number id="3DDA24DBD563FFD4FDF1E2455CB6F983" box="[620,652,1559,1585]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="13.0">13</number>
; anepisternals, 
<number id="3DDA24DBD563FFD4FCF3E2455D82F983" box="[878,952,1559,1585]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="13.5" valueMax="15.0" valueMin="12.0">12–15</number>
/ 
<number id="3DDA24DBD563FFD4FC5FE2455DCAF983" box="[962,1008,1559,1585]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="8.5" valueMax="9.0" valueMin="8.0">8–9</number>
; katepisternals, 
<number id="3DDA24DBD563FFD4FB44E2455B1FF983" box="[1241,1317,1559,1585]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="19.5" valueMax="21.0" valueMin="18.0">18–21</number>
; mesepimerals, 
<number id="3DDA24DBD563FFD4FE27E26D5FF3F9EB" box="[442,457,1599,1625]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="8.0">8</number>
/ 
<number id="3DDA24DBD563FFD4FE49E26D5FD9F9EB" box="[468,483,1599,1625]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="8.0">8</number>
; merals, 0; subspiraculars, 
<number id="3DDA24DBD563FFD4FCB6E26D5D60F9EB" box="[811,858,1599,1625]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="4.5" valueMax="6.0" valueMin="3.0">3–6</number>
; supra­alars, 
<number id="3DDA24DBD563FFD4FC66E26D5A10F9EB" box="[1019,1066,1599,1625]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="4.0" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="3.0">3–5</number>
; pedicelars, absent; a number of longer scutellar setae present, not in regular row. Wing (
<figureCitation id="13292A79D563FFD4FB8FE2355A63F933" box="[1042,1113,1639,1665]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="8.[264,368,912,936]" captionText="FIGURE 6. Anapausis wirthi. Holotype, wing." pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
Fig. 
<number id="3DDA24DBD563FFD4FBD5E2355A63F933" box="[1096,1113,1639,1665]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="6.0">6</number>
</figureCitation>
). M 
<number id="3DDA24DBD563FFD4FB15E2255AAAF937" box="[1160,1168,1655,1669]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="1.0">1</number>
long, broken at base; A 
<number id="3DDA24DBD563FFD4FE1DE2F05FB2F902" box="[384,392,1698,1712]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="1.0">1</number>
produced; cell m 
<number id="3DDA24DBD563FFD4FDC0E2C05C5DF91E" box="[605,615,1682,1708]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="1.0">1</number>
with 
<number id="3DDA24DBD563FFD4FD30E2C05C86F91E" box="[685,700,1682,1708]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="3.0">3</number>
macrotrichia; m 
<number id="3DDA24DBD563FFD4FC1EE2C05DFAF91E" box="[899,960,1682,1708]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="2.15">2, 15</number>
; m 
<number id="3DDA24DBD563FFD4FC7AE2C05A6AF91E" box="[999,1104,1682,1708]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="12.585" valueMax="21.0" valueMin="4.17">4, 17–21</number>
; cuA 
<number id="3DDA24DBD563FFD4FB0FE2C05AC0F91E" box="[1170,1274,1682,1708]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="8.55" valueMax="15.0" valueMin="2.1">2, 10–15</number>
; a 
<number id="3DDA24DBD563FFD4FA85E2C05F0DF964" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="3.2" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="1.4">1, 4–5</number>
. Abdomen. S 
<number id="3DDA24DBD563FFD4FE49E2EE5FD9F964" box="[468,483,1724,1750]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="6.0">6</number>
rectangular, unmodified. Male terminalia (
<figureCitation id="13292A79D563FFD4FC46E2EE5A18F964" box="[987,1058,1724,1750]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="8.[264,368,1787,1811]" captionTargetBox="[391,1199,995,1767]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[391,1199,989,1767]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 7. Anapausis wirthi. Holotype, male terminalia, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/173630/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
Fig. 
<number id="3DDA24DBD563FFD4FB8CE2EE5A18F964" box="[1041,1058,1724,1750]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="7.0">7</number>
</figureCitation>
). S 
<number id="3DDA24DBD563FFD4FBD5E2EE5A6DF964" box="[1096,1111,1724,1750]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="7.0">7</number>
with slight lateral projection, but definitely not lobose and well developed mesally; vesica well developed, pseudopenis present, distal tubular extension of aedeagus rather short; S 
<number id="3DDA24DBD563FFD4FBEBE35E5ABEF894" box="[1142,1156,1804,1830]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="8.0">8</number>
+ 
<number id="3DDA24DBD563FFD4FB08E35E5A9EF894" box="[1173,1188,1804,1830]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="9.0">9</number>
present as bare strip connected to T 
<number id="3DDA24DBD563FFD4FDD4E3665C6CF8FC" box="[585,598,1844,1870]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="8.0">8</number>
+ 
<number id="3DDA24DBD563FFD4FDFAE3665C4FF8FC" box="[615,629,1844,1870]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="9.0">9</number>
laterally; Gc unrecognizable; Gs present, deeply bifid, ventral extension setose, digitiform, dorsal extension more sclerotized, with single inner seta (
<figureCitation id="13292A79D56CFFDBFEDBE5165FA4FEEC" box="[326,414,324,350]" captionStart="FIGURES 8 – 10" captionStartId="9.[264,382,1054,1078]" captionTargetBox="[362,1231,326,1039]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[362,1231,326,1039]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 8 – 10. Anapausis wirthi. Holotype, male terminalia sclerites. 8. Sternite 10. 9. Parameres. 10. Gonostyle." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/173631/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
Fig. 
<number id="3DDA24DBD56CFFDBFEE3E5165FA4FEEC" box="[382,414,324,350]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="10.0">10</number>
</figureCitation>
); Pa well sclerotized, distally bifid (
<figureCitation id="13292A79D56CFFDBFCD4E5165DABFEEC" box="[841,913,324,350]" captionStart="FIGURES 8 – 10" captionStartId="9.[264,382,1054,1078]" captionTargetBox="[362,1231,326,1039]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[362,1231,326,1039]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 8 – 10. Anapausis wirthi. Holotype, male terminalia sclerites. 8. Sternite 10. 9. Parameres. 10. Gonostyle." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/173631/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
Fig. 
<number id="3DDA24DBD56CFFDBFC1DE5165DABFEEC" box="[896,913,324,350]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="9.0">9</number>
</figureCitation>
); S 
<number id="3DDA24DBD56CFFDBFC25E5165DECFEEC" box="[952,982,324,350]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="10.0">10</number>
completely divided into pair of digitiform distal sclerites with inner rounded tooth (
